value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the mitotic spindle pole body is broken into fragments.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of guanosine-diphosphatase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of guanosine-diphosphatase activity is decreased.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of guanosine-diphosphatase activity is increased.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of alpha,alpha-trehalase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of alpha,alpha-trehalase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: alpha,alpha-trehalase activity increase abolished during cellular response to nutrient

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of alpha,alpha-trehalase activity does not increase as a result of a nutrient stimulus.

label.value: alpha,alpha-trehalase activity increase abolished during cellular response to heat

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of alpha,alpha-trehalase activity does not increase as a result of a heat stimulus.

label.value: normal alpha,alpha-trehalase activity increase during cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of alpha,alpha-trehalase activity increases normally (i.e. as in wild type) as a result of oxidative stress.
A chemical response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cellular response to a nutrient is abnormal.

label.value: normal cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A cellular response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cellular response to oxidative stress is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal RNA level during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to salt stress is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal RNA level during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to heat is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to protamine sulfate. A protamine is any of a group of simple proteins that yield basic amino acids on hydrolysis, and forms a complex with heparin. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of protamine sulfate that allows wild type cells to grow.
A cell phenotype in which a cell is inviable in the phase of the life cycle during which wild type cells undergo vegetative growth.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable and longer than normal, and has a greater length:diameter ratio than normal.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell is viable.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is viable and longer than normal, and has a greater length:diameter ratio than normal.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, is elongated, and contains more than one nucleus apiece.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, is elongated, and contains more than one septum.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is viable, is elongated, and contains more than one nucleus.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is viable, is elongated, and contain more than one septum.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: inviable elongated cell with mitotic cell cycle arrest in interphase

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable and elongated, and progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in interphase. The cell contains one nucleus and no septum.

definition.value: A population of cells with this phenotype usually shows a marginal increase in cell number before all cells die. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to cytochalasin B. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of cytochalasin B that allows wild type cells to grow.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of cytochalasin B than normal.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing cytochalasin B.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to brefeldin A. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of brefeldin A that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased cellular trehalose level during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of trehalose measured in a cell is higher than normal during a cellular response to osmotic stress.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of alpha,alpha-trehalase activity is lower than normal during sporulation.

label.value: decreased cellular trehalose level during sporulation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of trehalose measured in a cell is lower than normal during sporulation.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylserine measured in a cell is higher than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylcholine measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished protein localization to chromatin during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: viable vegetative cell, abnormal cell shape, normal cell size

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell is viable, cell shape is altered, and cell size remains normal, in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: inviable vegetative cell, abnormal cell shape, normal cell size

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell is inviable, cell shape is altered, and cell size remains normal, in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is branched and elongated.

definition.value: These cells often form a branch at a non-right angle to the long axis of the mother cell.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic sister chromatid segregation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Mitotic sister chromatid segregation is the entire process in which replicated homologous chromosomes are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two sets during the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal telomere tethering at nuclear periphery during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which telomere tethering at the nuclear periphery is abnormal.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of mercury ions than normal.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of aluminium ions than normal.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of diethyl maleate than normal.

definition.value: Note that diethyl maleate should not be written without a space, as diethylmaleate is a different compound.

label.value: increased cellular glutathione level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of glutathione (GSH) measured in a cell is higher than normal.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing caffeine.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing leptomycin B.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of L-thialysine than normal.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to L-thialysine. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of L-thialysine that allows wild type cells to grow.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing L-thialysine.
